<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-10-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-10-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="786" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d786">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Loomis</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi></placeName>,<lb/><date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-10-19"><hi rend="italic">October
                                        19, 1899</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The revolution practically over. The President of Venezuela will probably
                            leave Caracas and Castro enter within forty-eight hours without
                            fighting.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Loomis.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>